data.text: @bonnieallan72 @juliette_io @dbRaevn Thanks. Yes, looking through their feeds data looks to be available. Well presented.
@crsddn @juliette_io This is the only recent one I’ve seen from @dbRaevn https://t.co/nJm8UKSNW1
@bonnieallan72 @juliette_io Not sure on Vic. I haven’t seen anyone produce. It should be standardised across states unfortunately. Data transparency very low overall.
@crsddn @juliette_io Is there any Vic data on age groups affected recently ?

@bonnieallan72 @juliette_io Realised link was not copied. Data available on charts only for 0-9 & 10-20. Daily scraped. 

https://t.co/m8KYoxhrTA
@juliette_io Is there an estimate for an Reff in this age group?

@juliette_io It’s %age increases in the 60+ age groups I look at more than anything. That’s where severe outcomes are strongly weighted. So would prefer to see the growth being in younger groups, but it’s not that clearcut.
@juliette_io Things would look very different if all other age groups were also recommended to do twice weekly RATs and given 5 free RATs per fortnight.

@RichardfromSyd1 @juliette_io @s_n_morris I'd suggest the word to describe it "minimised" :-).

The hospitalisations by age are a snapshot, and this won't/shouldn't reconcile to the (prone to decrease) cumulative totals.

@juliette_io @s_n_morris It is more 'cut down' then different.

For example, the data on death by vax status and age together has been dropped
